-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Third-Party Software
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The lazybv2int source code uses third-party software which has its own
copyright and licensing terms, as described below.

- lazybv2int uses the MathSAT SMTLIB Parser via MathSAT API. The MathSAT license is 
restricted to research-only usage. For more details, see 
https://mathsat.fbk.eu/download.html

- lazybv2int uses CVC4 to solve formulas over arithmetics and uninterpreted functions. 
This dependency is compatible with the BSD license above. 
For more details, see https://github.com/CVC4/CVC4

- lazybv2int uses smt-switch as an interface to the other solvers. 
This dependency is compatible with the BSD license above. 
For more details, see https://github.com/makaimann/smt-switch/
